  "prompt": "What is the best way to remove permanent marker from a countertop?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to remove permanent marker from a countertop:\n\n1. Rubbing Alcohol\n- Apply rubbing alcohol to a cloth\n- Gently rub the marker stain\n- Highly effective on many surfaces\n\n2. Magic Eraser\n- Use a Mr. Clean Magic Eraser\n- Gently scrub the stained area\n- Works well on many countertop materials\n\n3. Hand Sanitizer\n- Contains alcohol\n- Apply to the stain and wipe with a clean cloth\n- Typically safe for most surfaces\n\n4. Dry Erase Marker\n- Draw over the permanent marker with a dry erase marker\n- Immediately wipe away with a clean cloth\n- Works surprisingly well on some surfaces\n\n5. Toothpaste\n- Use non-gel white toothpaste\n- Rub gently with a cloth\n- Rinse thoroughly after cleaning\n\n6. Acetone/Nail Polish Remover\n- Use sparingly and carefully\n- Test in an inconspicuous area first\n- Not recommended for all countertop materials\n\nAlways test any cleaning method in a small, hidden area first to ensure it doesn't damage the surface, and be gentle to avoid scratching.",
